# Copy to .env and fill in. .env is gitignored — NEVER commit the real one.
# Everything personal or secret lives here, so this repo stays publishable.
#
# ⚠️ .env HOLDS SECRETS, NOT POLICY.
# Do not put tool allowlists or behaviour here. Each job script exports its own
# least-privilege tool set, and run-agent.sh makes the CALLER win over anything set here.
# (This is not theoretical: .env once defined AGENT_ALLOWED_TOOLS and silently stripped
# Gmail from the morning brief. The brief asked for it, .env took it away, every MCP call
# was denied, and the model dutifully reported "0 threads found." Fixed 2026-07-14.)

# ── REQUIRED ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Where the private context repo is checked out. NOTE: this is the repo itself,
# not its parent. Getting this wrong makes every job read the wrong CLAUDE.md.
CONTEXT_DIR="$HOME/agent/my-context"

# The workspace root (the directory containing BOTH repos).
WORKSPACE_DIR="$HOME/agent"

# Phone push. REQUIRED — without it, a failing job fails SILENTLY, which is the
# single most dangerous state this system can be in.
# The topic is a de-facto secret: anyone who knows it can push to your phone,
# and anyone who guesses it can READ your briefs. Make it long and random.
NTFY_URL="https://ntfy.sh"
NTFY_TOPIC="pick-something-long-and-random"

# OPTIONAL — a second topic for routine/fyi pushes (2026-07-17 two-tier split), so
# "your backup failed" and "task added" don't buzz your phone at equal weight. Subscribe
# to BOTH topics in the ntfy app; set THIS one to silent/badge-only, keep the other loud.
# If unset, fyi-tier pushes fall back to NTFY_TOPIC above — nothing is ever dropped, just
# not separated until you set this.
# NTFY_TOPIC_FYI="pick-a-different-long-random-string"

# ── GUARDRAILS (see the header of scripts/run-agent.sh) ───────────────────────
# A scheduled agent must be bounded in TIME, CONCURRENCY, and FREQUENCY.
# Any one of these left unbounded is an unbounded bill.

AGENT_MAX_TURNS=25            # tool-call depth per run
AGENT_TIMEOUT_SEC=600         # hard wall-clock kill. `claude -p` CAN hang.
AGENT_MAX_RUNS_PER_DAY=12     # CIRCUIT BREAKER. Trips, refuses, and pages you.
                              # This is the guard that catches a genuine runaway loop.
AGENT_MAX_CONCURRENT=2        # CONCURRENCY CAP for deep-work agents (spawn-agent.sh).
                              # The per-job flock only stops a job stacking on ITSELF; this
                              # bounds the TOTAL running at once. Keep small on an 8GB box.
AGENT_LOG_DIR="$HOME/.agent-logs"
BACKUP_DIR="$HOME/backups"

# Fallback tool set ONLY — every job overrides this. Do not widen it.
AGENT_ALLOWED_TOOLS="Read,Glob,Grep"

# ── Message bus (scripts/bus.py) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# The SQLite coordination store that spawned agents + your parallel chats write to,
# so one seat can see and steer the fleet. This is a PATH (safe here), not behaviour.
# OPTIONAL — leave it unset and it defaults to $CONTEXT_DIR/local-only/agent_bus.db,
# which is gitignored AND inside the nightly backup tarball, so message content never
# reaches GitHub. Only set it to move the DB, and it MUST stay under local-only/: the
# PII gate skips binaries, so the DB's only protection is its location.
# BUS_DB="$CONTEXT_DIR/local-only/agent_bus.db"

# ── GitHub: let the agent READ your code (scripts/sync-repos.sh) ──────────────
# PUBLIC repos need NO TOKEN — sync-repos.sh auto-discovers them from the API,
# including any you create later. Public is public.
GITHUB_USER="your-github-handle"

# Upstreams you don't own but whose code you need (e.g. a repo you send PRs to).
GITHUB_UPSTREAMS="someorg/some-repo"

# A token is needed ONLY for PRIVATE repos.
#   https://github.com/settings/personal-access-tokens/new
#   Repository access : "Only select repositories"  ← NEVER "All repositories"
#   Permissions       : Contents / Metadata / Issues / Pull requests = READ-ONLY
#
# ⚠️ NEVER use an all-repository token. Your private context repo holds your entire
# life, the agent already has it locally, and the agent reads untrusted email and web
# content while holding shell access — every token it carries is a blast radius.
# GITHUB_TOKEN="github_pat_..."
# GITHUB_PRIVATE_REPOS="you/private-one you/private-two"
# CODEBASES_DIR="$HOME/agent/codebases"

# ── Optional ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Canvas/LMS calendar feed. Treat as a secret — it's an unauthenticated link to
# your whole schedule.
# CANVAS_ICS_URL="https://canvas.example.edu/feeds/calendars/user_....ics"

# Read-only infrastructure token, so the agent can audit but never destroy.
# HCLOUD_TOKEN="..."
